<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINES, CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12
        ENGINES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Testing Electrical Power Supply to ECM
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Testing Electrical Power Supply to ECM</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Procedure in
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0823701">Testing Switched Power Supply To ECM</hotlnk>
                tests the switched battery power circuits to the ECM (key on).
            </para>
            <para>Procedure in
                <hotlnk xrefid="x0823704">Testing Unswitched Battery Feed To ECM</hotlnk>
                tests the unswitched battery power circuits to the ECM.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823701">
            <title>Testing Switched Power Supply To ECM</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (1014) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0823701" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Switched Power Supply To ECM</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.61in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.62in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.93in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.83in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.27in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove and check fuse F11-B for open condition. Fuses OK?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F11-B</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse(s).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect conn. (1014) from ECM. Re-install fuse F11-B. Turn key on and measure
                                    voltage to gnd. at terminal 70, circuit 97L.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(1014), 97L to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Perform
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0823702">Testing Run Relay (64).</hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Switched voltage to ECM checks good. At connector (1014), measure voltage between
                                    terminals 5 (circuit 97-G) and 70 (circuit 97L).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(1014), between 97-G and 97L.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>ECM gnd. circuit 97-GA checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in ground circuit 97-GA, between conn. (1014) and
                                    engine ground stud, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823702">
            <title>Testing Run Relay (64)</title>
            <table id="t0823702" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Run Relay (64)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.60in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.20in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove run relay from socket (64). Turn key on. At (64) measure voltage to ground
                                    at circuit 97C.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(64), 97C to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 97C, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At relay socket (64) measure voltage between circuits 97C and 11-DB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(64) between 97C and 11-DB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connec- tion in circuit 11-DB to panel light ground, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At relay socket (64) measure voltage between circuits 97A and 11-DB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(64) between 97A and 11-DB.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Perform
                                    <hotlnk xrefid="x0823703">Testing Ignition Relay</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At relay socket (64), install jumper wire between 97C and 97L. At connector (1014)
                                    measure voltage between terminal 70 (circuit 97L) and ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(1014) between 97L and gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the run relay in conn. (64).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connec- tion in circuit 97L between connectors (64) and
                                    (1014), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823703">
            <title>Testing Ignition Relay (R6)</title>
            <table id="t0823703" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Ignition Relay (R6)</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
