                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove and check fuses F5-B and F4-B for open condition. Fuses OK?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>F5-B, F4-B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse(s).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off/ On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Re-install fuses F5-B and F4-B. Remove relay from socket (R6). Turn key on. At
                                    socket (R6) measure voltage from circuit 13G to gnd.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(R6), 13G to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage from B1 to BAT stud, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (R6) measure voltage between circuits 14AA and 13-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(R6) between 14AA and 13-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 13-G path to ground, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (R6) measure voltage between circuits 13A and 13-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(R6) between 13A and 13-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage in circuit 13A from key switch, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (R6) install jumper wire between circuits 14AA and 13A. At run relay
                                    connector (64) measure voltage to ground at circuit 97A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(64), 97A to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace ignition relay in conn. (R6).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuits 13A and 97A between conn. (R6),
                                    ignition adapter and conn. (64), then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x0823704">
            <title>Testing Unswitched Battery Feed To ECM</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Disconnecting (1014) from the ECM will cause incremental amounts of Trip Data to be lost. An
                        "Event Recorder Data Lost" code may also be logged. The loss of this data will not affect engine
                        operation, but will affect the accuracy of the data. Ask the owner/operator if they want data
                        recorded before disconnecting.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
